<title>UK: Baltic Handy Index down eight at 1,059.</title>
<headline>Baltic Handy Index down eight at 1,059.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-05-29</dateline>
<text>
<p>The Baltic Handy Index for Handy size shipping rates fell to 1,059 on Thursday from 1,067 on May 27, with the base being Jan 7 1997 equals 1000. The BHI is based on the following routes with rates in dollars/tonne.</p>
<p> Route					 Weighting   Average   Prev</p>
<p>								   ($/Day)</p>
<p>1. Continent/Far East			 25 pct    13,067  13,280</p>
<p>2. Japan-S.Korea/NoPac or Australia RV  30	   8,613   8,630</p>
<p>3. Singapore/Australia/Continent	  15	   5,525   5,530</p>
<p>4. Continent/N or S.Atlantic RV	   30	   8,410   8,488</p>
<p>(All for 43,000 DWT)</p>
<p>Ongoing Trial Routes					     $/MT</p>
<p>T1 1.4-1.6 M 55' USG/Continent-Grains    -	    15.06  15.56</p>
<p>T2 28/32,000 53' Brazil/Continent-Grains -	    17.63  17.79</p>
<p>Note - The Index initially to be published each Tuesday and Thursday is derived from four Handymax time charter routes based on the 'Baltic Handy Max', a modern 43,000 DWT vessel with 25 ton cranes.  The Baltic Exchange will also publish returns on two other trial routes alongside the Index. They may be included in it at a later date.</p>
<p>London Newsroom, +44 171 542 7771</p>
